    <!-- Application Structure Plan:
         1. Header: Title and Vision Statement.
         2. Executive Dashboard: High-level metrics on the 2026 Job Market shift (Why this program exists).
         3. The Core Roadmap (Interactive Tabs): A 6-semester breakdown. Users click tabs to see specific modules, tools, and outcomes for each semester.
         4. Skill Shift Analysis (Radar Chart): Visualizing the transition from "Syntax" to "Orchestration".
         5. The Tool Stack (Grid): Detailed breakdown of specific tools (Cursor, Claude, etc.) and their specific use cases in the curriculum.
         6. Project Gallery: Examples of capstone projects students will build.
         Rationale: This structure moves from "Why" (Market Data) to "What" (Roadmap) to "How" (Tools/Skills), allowing the professor to present a compelling case to the administration or students.
    -->

